article.headline: Sacred Heart 92, Fairleigh Dickinson 81
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Drew Shubik had 16 points, 14 rebounds, nine assists and three steals to lead Sacred Heart to a 92-81 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday. Brice Brooks added 17 points and Luke Granato had 14 for the Pioneers (12-10, 9-2 Northeast Conference), while Ryon Howard finished with 12 points and 10 rebounds. Manny Ubilla had 29 points and nine assists for the Knights (6-13, 2-7), while Eric Hazard had 16 points and DeJuan Pursley added 14 points and seven rebounds. FDU jumped out to an early 18-10 lead, but Sacred Heart fought back and led 48-43 at the half. The Pioneers took command midway through the second half as Shubik scored eight unanswered points to give his team a 67-53 lead, and the Knights would not get closer than nine points down the rest of the way. Sacred Heart outrebounded FDU 43-32.
